story_txt:
Short SummaryI want to use my extensive knowledge of the written word to create a 3-month travelogue about a very bad person being very mean. Because, well, strokes.Less-Short Summary
 Hi, I'm MCM, and I write stuff. In the last decade, I created a TV show called RollBots, wrote a whole bunch of books like The Pig and the Box, Typhoon and Fission Chips, and tried to push the publishing envelope in crazy new directions. My newest project, Shutterbugs, a preschool show I co-created, is currently in production.For my next trick, I want to write a story about an insufferable bastard being insufferably bastardly... so I don't die.Now I know what you're thinking: how can writing a story keep someone alive? Well, I've got insanely high blood pressure thanks to two awful years helping my wife recover from being hit by a car, and thanks to the abject failure of the insurance industry, I don't know how I'm going to keep the lights on for the next three months. Literally, even. And while my doctor thinks pills are the answer, I can tell you with some certainty that pills cost money, which to me sounds like a negative feedback loop in action. So I'm opting for the natural approach: I want to write something cathartic, with no regard for human decency, to help relieve the stress that's killing me.And thus, we have Sriracha for the Soul, a travelogue about a broken-down bastard who is sent by God to savagely belittle enough people to avert the apocalypse. And no, God hasn't been drinking. Yet.The story will be published free on the web, in chapters no more than 1,000 words, twice a week, until the end of August. There is a plot, and a purpose, and it will be viciously funny to see it unfold.Why is this project important to me? If it gets funded, it helps me feed my family. And if it doesn't, at least I'll be happier while I starve to death. Ha ha, just kidding. Sorta.What We Need & What You Get How much does this cost? Here's what's needed for me to write this: $3,000. Not because it costs money for me to smack my hands against the keyboard, but because that's the shortfall in my summer budget... it's what's keeping me from reaching September in one piece. My summer budget has no frills in it, either. Sadly. I need me some Screech.What kinds of perks will you get? Sadly, pretty much just good vibes. The goal here is to make my life LESS stressful, not more. But my good vibes, they're A1 good vibes, 100% certified by the Good Vibes Association of Canada, which may or may not exist.What if you don't get to $3,000? Well, I'll still write it, but I'll cry a little every time I post a chapter. But probably not much, because I'll be dehydrated and stuff.  OK, But Seriously, What?The premise to the story is simple: God calls upon Cal McIver to piss off the AntiChrist, thereby saving the world.Cal is a guy with a silver tongue that he regularly misuses, so it's a bit of a shock when he's chosen for this Very Important Mission. But desperate times call for desperate measures...See, the apocalypse is coming, and thanks to some legal fine print, the supreme commander of the Armies of Hell must be chosen randomly from a pool of living mortals with True Hate in their hearts. So that can either be a diabolical murderer on death row, or... a cyclist who gets chewed out about not stopping at stop signs.The Lord works in mysterious ways, the clever bastard.The Impact How will Sriracha for the Soul change the world? I'm fairly certain it'll kill a hefty number of brain cells in anyone who reads it, so... er... that's something. And hey, it might make you smile. If it does, you may want to see a psychiatrist.How can you trust that I can do this? Well, I have a pretty solid track record in terms of writing, and writing on odd schedules (see: The Archivists, written in three straight days, jet lagged in Belgium, while a large audience voted to meddle with my plot points). Next to all that, this is easy. Risks & Challenges Risks. Well, I might die midway through. That's a risk for sure. In terms of challenges, I occasionally get migraines due to weather, and that'd definitely slow things down. But in the end, there's nothing in this that I can't handle. Except the death part.   Other Ways You Can Help If you have no money, that's fine. I have no money, and I still love me. But if you want to help while being broke (or even while rich!) you can do the following:
Tell your friends about this;
Tell your enemies that you hate this and would never support it;
Use the Indiegogo share tools;
Don't get hit by a car;
Send me a happy email at mcm@1889.ca, because I like happy.
Thank you, and good night.
